Several works have analyzed the potential of larger LMs, specifically GPT-3 and GPT-4,. 
They investigate few-shot prompting for extracting factual knowledge for KBC [alivanistos2023prompting] or for making the factual knowledge in a LM more explicit [cohen2023crawling].
These models can aid in building a knowledge base on Wikidata or improving the interpretability of LMs. Despite the variance in the precision of extracted facts from GPT-3, it can peak at over 90% for some relations.